  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, how was the team meeting about the new app feature?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was good, we discussed the UI changes. The team is excited. I have a cricket match this weekend, by the way. Should be fun."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Nice to hear the meeting went well! Excitement is contagious. Cricket matches are always fun — what position are you playing?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm playing as a batsman, but I also bowl sometimes. The weather looks good, so the match should be enjoyable. I'm really looking forward to it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Good — batsmen and bowlers need clear skies! The weather makes all the difference. Will you be watching any Bollywood movies this weekend too?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, maybe I'll watch a Bollywood movie Sunday. I like the new ones with Ranbir Kapoor. They usually have good stories. But I might be too tired after the match. Aapne koi accha film dekha hai?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — Ranbir Kapoor's movies often have great stories. It's easy to get tired after a match, so rest is important. I've seen Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara — it's a fun watch. Do you prefer action or romantic stories more?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, generally I like romantic stories more. The action ones are good too, but sometimes they feel too much. Have you seen Laaga Chunari Mera Dil? It's an old one, but I think it's really nice."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — romantic stories are more your style. Laaga Chunari Mera Dil is a lovely film with strong characters. Do you have a favourite song from it?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The song \"Chunariyaan\" is my favourite from that movie. It's so classic and sweet. I don't know why, but I still hum it sometimes. Do you like old Hindi songs?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Classic songs like 'Chunariyaan' stick with you for a reason — they're beautiful. I enjoy old Hindi songs too, especially when they feel timeless. What's one you hum often?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yehuda\" from Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham is another one I often sing. It's very emotional. Old songs have a charm that new ones sometimes lack. I should go now, thanks for the chat!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Right — 'Yehuda' is emotional and full of feeling. Old songs do have a special charm. Tell me, did you try adding tomatoes to the moong dal?\""
    }
  ],
